npm-packages/
# Root tests/ holds Playwright specs, Node E2E and node-based unit tests - none
# of it is Meteor code, and Meteor's file watcher otherwise churns on the
# tests/playwright/test-results/ tree (inotify errors). Ignore everything under
# root tests/ EXCEPT tests/main.js, which is meteor.testModule (see package.json)
# and imports the server/client Mocha suites. Those suites live under
# server/lib/tests/ and client/lib/tests/ - NOT under root tests/ - so a naked
# "tests/" (which matches a dir named tests at any depth) must NOT be used here,
# or it would hide them and `meteor test` would report "0 passing".
/tests/*
!/tests/main.js
